items.sentence: If you\'re not busy, could you please help me?
I had not waited ten minutes before Mary came.
I had some questions that I wanted to ask Tom.
I had the porter take my suitcases to my room.
I had to give Tom more time to think about it.
I had to make a list of things I needed to do.
She expected him to buy her an expensive gift.
She grinned at me when she came into the room.
She has an extremely expressive singing voice.
She kept on talking after I asked her to stop.
Tom said he didn\'t really care what happened.
Tom said he doesn\'t know how to speak French.
Tom was ticketed for passing on a yellow line.
Tom doesn\'t like the way Mary treats her dog.
Tom doesn\'t like working on an empty stomach.
Tom doesn\'t look like the man in the picture.
Tom doesn\'t need to get up so early tomorrow.
Tom doesn\'t need to know where Mary is going.
Tom doesn\'t need to know who gave this to us.
Tom said he had been asked a lot of questions.
